<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="18" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[113,772,1197,2053]" lastBlockId="19.[816,1474,1096,1249]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">
Prendini &amp; Loria (2020: 442) formally synonymized 
<taxonomicName authority="Borelli, 1919" authorityName="Borelli" authorityYear="1919" box="[113,503,1229,1253]" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Pandinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedius">
<emphasis box="[113,350,1229,1253]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Pandinus intermedius</emphasis>
Borelli, 1919
</taxonomicName>
under 
<taxonomicName authority="Borelli, 1919" authorityName="Borelli" authorityYear="1919" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Pandinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="citernii">
<emphasis box="[584,771,1229,1253]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Pandinus citernii</emphasis>
Borelli, 1919
</taxonomicName>
(both now in the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fet" authorityYear="1997" box="[566,690,1261,1285]" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Pandinurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[566,690,1261,1285]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Pandinurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), “ 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">two Ethiopian species of</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fet" authorityYear="1997" box="[354,474,1293,1317]" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Pandinurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pandinurus</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">
described from the same 
<typeStatus box="[113,157,1326,1349]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">type</typeStatus>
locality
</emphasis>
”, without explanation of their taxonomic act. In their paragraph, the authors cited only “ 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">unpublished data</emphasis>
”. They did not address previously proposed diagnostic characters, in particular chelal trichobothrium 
<emphasis box="[633,658,1422,1445]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">ea</emphasis>
, which is present in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Borelli" authorityYear="1919" box="[224,376,1453,1477]" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Pandinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedius">
<emphasis box="[224,376,1453,1477]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">P. intermedius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and absent in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Borelli" authorityYear="1919" box="[529,632,1454,1477]" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Pandinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="citernii">
<emphasis box="[529,632,1454,1477]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">P. citernii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and ignored other morphological characters published in KovařÍk et al. (2017c). They characterized these as “Ethiopian” species, although the originally cited 
<typeStatus box="[462,508,1549,1573]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">type</typeStatus>
localities are actually located in 
<collectingCountry box="[227,318,1581,1605]" name="Somalia" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Somalia</collectingCountry>
. In fact, two separate areas of distribution in 
<collectingCountry box="[142,232,1613,1637]" name="Ethiopia" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Ethiopia</collectingCountry>
were indeed confirmed by KovařÍk et al. (2017c). However, the co-occurrence of both species at “the same 
<typeStatus box="[725,771,1645,1669]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">type</typeStatus>
locality” in 
<collectingCountry box="[245,332,1677,1701]" name="Somalia" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Somalia</collectingCountry>
had not been confirmed. Borelli (1919) studied specimens collected by Carlo Citerni, and there is a significant possibility that Citerni did not personally collect these specimens and assign locality labels himself. It has been repeatedly documented that old specimens in Italian museums are labelled with imprecise localities, and their true geographic distributions need to be independently confirmed (see also KovařÍk et al, 2019: 61). The confirmed distributions of both the species in 
<collectingCountry box="[357,450,1933,1957]" name="Ethiopia" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Ethiopia</collectingCountry>
, as well as their unconfirmed 
<typeStatus box="[113,159,1965,1989]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">type</typeStatus>
locality in 
<collectingCountry box="[286,376,1965,1989]" name="Somalia" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Somalia</collectingCountry>
, are mapped in 
<figureCitation box="[553,634,1965,1989]" captionStart="Figure 83" captionStartId="20.[113,181,2018,2040]" captionTargetBox="[113,1474,944,2005]" captionTargetId="figure-31@20.[113,1474,941,2005]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figure 83. Map showing confirmed distribution of Pandinurus spp." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4648868" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4648868/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Fig. 83</figureCitation>
. In addition, recent DNA and chromosomal analysis further supports the view that both are separate and valid species. For example, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Borelli" authorityYear="1919" box="[816,975,1096,1120]" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Pandinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedius">
<emphasis box="[816,975,1096,1120]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">P. intermedius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a constant number of chromosomes of 2n=110, whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Borelli" authorityYear="1919" box="[1021,1133,1129,1152]" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Pandinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="citernii">
<emphasis box="[1021,1133,1129,1152]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">P. citernii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a different and constant number of chromosomes of 2n=120 (
<bibRefCitation author="STUNDLOVA" box="[1233,1418,1161,1187]" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" refId="ref6739" refString="STUNDLOVA, J. 2019. Mechanisms of the karyotype evolution in scorpions (Arachnida: Scorpiones). Ph. D. Dissertation, Department of Zoology, Charles University of Prague, Czech Republic." type="book" year="2019">ŠtundlovÁ, 2019</bibRefCitation>
). We therefore reinstate 
<taxonomicName authority="(Borelli, 1919)" baseAuthorityName="Borelli" baseAuthorityYear="1919" box="[1019,1444,1192,1217]" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Pandinurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="intermedius">
<emphasis box="[1019,1277,1192,1216]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">Pandinurus intermedius</emphasis>
(Borelli, 1919)
</taxonomicName>
as a valid species distinct from 
<taxonomicName authority="(Borelli, 1919)" baseAuthorityName="Borelli" baseAuthorityYear="1919" box="[1122,1394,1224,1249]" class="Arachnida" family="Scorpionidae" genus="Pandinus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="19" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="citernii">
<emphasis box="[1122,1225,1225,1248]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="18">P. citernii</emphasis>
(Borelli, 1919)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
